Steps:

Go to AWS Console → Route 53
Click Hosted Zones → Create Hosted Zone
Enter:
Domain name (e.g., example.com)
Type: Public Hosted Zone
Note the Name Servers (NS records)
Go to your domain registrar (e.g., GoDaddy) and update nameservers
Create a Record:
Type: A (for EC2) or CNAME (for domain mapping)
Value: EC2 public IP / Load Balancer DNS
Save and wait for DNS propagation
